docs.title: Programming with that simply works.
docs.text:
1. No pointers
  2. No complex "this"(in javascript, "this" is difficult. for example. "this" in window, "this" in function, "this" in classes' methods, staticmethods And more others)
  3. There is nothing particularly difficult.
  4. Don't care about memory1 at all.

docs.title: Everything you would expect.
docs.text:
• Very simple
  • Easy to expand
  • Functional programming
  • Working in Terminal(with CPython)
  • Open Source

docs.title: Type of UEL
docs.text: The UEL is a dynamic typing, interpreted, and very fast language.

docs.title: Install by python-pip
docs.text:
If you are a user, It's very simple. use the pip 

pip install uel

docs.title: Install from sources
docs.text:
make
If you cached binary of UEL's extensions, You can using 
make install
